(1) A person shall not— (a) delay, assault, threaten or obstruct an authorised officer in the performance of the authorised officer ’s functions; (b) refuse to give an authorised officer reasonable assistance that the authorised officer may require for the purpose of exercising the authorised officer ’s powers; (c) give an authorised officer false or misleading information in answer to an inquiry made by the authorised officer ; or (d) impersonate an authorised officer or present oneself to be an authorised officer .
